tyles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/butter.jpg?itok=WmVkxpe0" width="100" height="100" alt="Butter" title="Butter" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/butter">Butter</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">butt-err</span><p>Butter is made when lactic-acid producing bacteria are added to cream and churned to make an…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g plain flour">50g plain flour</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="600ml milk">600ml <a href="/glossary/milk" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">milk</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-260691" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/milk"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/milk-resized.jpg?itok=z-tC0wLi" width="100" height="100" alt="" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/milk">Milk</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">mill-k</span><p>One of the most widely used ingredients, milk is often referred to as a complete food. While cow…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 tsp Dijon mustard">1 tsp Dijon mustard</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 x 195g cans tuna, drained">2 x 195g cans <a href="/glossary/tuna" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">tuna</a>, drained<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-252036" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/tuna"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/tuna.jpg?itok=8T9-jfhU" width="100" height="100" alt="Tuna" title="A member of the mackerel family, tuna are mainly found in the world&#039;s warmer oceans" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/tuna">Tuna</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">tune-ah</span><p>A member of the mackerel family, tuna are mainly found in the world's warmer oceans. They…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="4 spring onions, sliced">4 <a href="/glossary/spring-onion" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">spring onions</a>, sliced<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-252336" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/spring-onion"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/springonions.jpg?itok=Vrl_tEXh" width="100" height="100" alt="Spring onions" title="Also known as scallions or green onions, spring onions are in fact very young onions, harvested before the bulb has had a chance to swell" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/spring-onion">Spring onion</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">sp-ring un-yun</span><p>Also known as scallions or green onions, spring onions are in fact very young onions, harvested…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="198g can sweetcorn, drained">198g can <a href="/glossary/sweetcorn" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">sweetcorn</a>, drained<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-252341" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/sweetcorn"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/sweetcorn.jpg?itok=-1CXLCu7" width="100" height="100" alt="Sweetcorn" title="Also known as corn on the cob, sweetcorn is composed of rows of tightly packed golden yellow kernels, growing along a tough central core" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sweetcorn">Sweetcorn</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">sw-eet corn</span><p>Also known as corn on the cob, sweetcorn is composed of rows of tightly packed golden yellow…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="100g cheddar, grated">100g <a href="/glossary/cheddar" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--6 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">cheddar</a>, grated<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--6"><article id="node-5805131" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/cheddar"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2016/04/cheddar.jpg?itok=OyKhh-0b" width="100" height="100" alt="Cheddar" title="Cheddar" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/cheddar">Cheddar</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">Ched-ah</span><p>Once cheddar was 'Cheddar', a large, hard-pressed barrel of cheese made by a particular…</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Bring a pan of water to the boil. Add the pasta and cook, following pack instructions, until tender. Add the peas for the final 3 mins cooking time.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Meanwhile, melt the butter in a pan over a medium heat. Stir in the flour and cook for 2 mins. Add the milk, whisking constantly, then slowly bring to the boil, stirring often, until sauce thickens. Remove from the heat, add the mustard and season well.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat the grill to medium. Drain the pasta and peas, then return to the pan and stir in the tuna, spring onions, sweetcorn and sauce. Tip into a shallow baking dish, top with the cheddar and cook under the grill for 5 mins or until golden and bubbling.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1328054400" class="text-style-alt">February 2012</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-bo